==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Profanity
<hw>Pro*fan"i*ty</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[L.
<ets>profanitas</ets>.]</ety>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>1.</sn> <def>The quality or state of being profane; profaneness;
irreverence; esp., the use of profane language; blasphemy.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>That which is profane; profane language or
acts.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>The brisk interchange of <qex>profanity</qex> and folly.</q>
<rj><qau>Buckminster.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Profection</ent>⟦br⟧
